data.text:
The Center for the Study of Western Hemispheric Trade (CSWHT) at Texas A&M International University is a public service institute founded to study globalization with special emphasis on the Western Hemisphere. The Center is a part of the A. R. Sanchez, Jr. School of Business.

The Center seeks to increase awareness and knowledge about Western Hemispheric countries and their economic, political, and social interactions.

The CSWHT is a unique, leading research facility that, along with its allied components and key contacts throughout the Western Hemisphere, provides current and relevant information about issues dealing with trade and commerce that affect its constituents in the Hemisphere.
